---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="💀 Datablock — CyperX.dev" activeNav="datablock">

  <!-- Chaos Stickers (sm+) -->
  <div class="chaos-sticker sticker-red hidden sm:block" style="position: absolute; top: 6%; right: 4%; z-index: 40; pointer-events: none;">NEURAL_SKATE</div>
  <div class="chaos-sticker sticker-cyan hidden sm:block" style="position: absolute; bottom: 12%; left: 2%; z-index: 40; pointer-events: none;">OPENCLAW_BOT</div>
  <div class="chaos-sticker sticker-acid hidden md:block" style="position: absolute; top: 50%; right: 3%; z-index: 40; pointer-events: none; transform: rotate(-4deg);">KICKFLIP_AI</div>

  <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto relative z-10">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <header class="mb-8 sm:mb-16 relative">
      <div class="ghost-skull-bg hidden sm:flex">
      ______
   .-"      "-.
  /            \
 |,  .-.  .-.  ,|
 | )(__/  \__)( |
 |/     /\     \|
 (_     ^^     _)
  \__|IIIIII|__/
   | \IIIIII/ |
   \          /
    `--------`
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-[36px] sm:text-[60px] md:text-[90px] leading-[0.8] text-white uppercase glitch-shadow-intense break-words mb-4 sm:mb-8 relative z-10">
        BUILDING THE<br />
        <span class="text-primary chromatic-aberration" data-text="OPENCLAW">OPENCLAW</span><br />
        NEURAL-SKATE
      </h1>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 sm:gap-4 font-mono text-xs sm:text-sm">
        <span class="text-muted font-bold">&gt; TS: 1718293400</span>
        <span class="corrupt-meta font-bold">[FRAG: CLAUDE]</span>
        <span class="corrupt-meta font-bold">[FRAG: OPENCLAW]</span>
        <span class="corrupt-meta font-bold hidden sm:inline" style="animation-delay: 0.5s;">[FRAG: HALLUCINATION]</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <article class="space-y-8 sm:space-y-12 text-white relative">
      <p class="text-base sm:text-[24px]">
        The mainframe told me it couldn't map the transition of a halfpipe. I told it to shut the fuck up and fed it 200 hours of corrupted 90s VHS skate tapes through <span class="text-primary font-mono underline decoration-accent-red decoration-2 underline-offset-4">Claude Code</span>. The result? A neural network that thinks a kickflip is a <span class="font-bold text-accent-red px-1">buffer overflow</span>.
      </p>

      <p class="opacity-90 text-sm sm:text-base">
        We wired the OpenClaw actuators directly into the deck. No dampening. Pure brutalist feedback. When the bot hits the coping, it dumps a stack trace into my local terminal like a digital vomit of <span class="text-acid">pure logic</span>.
      </p>

      <div class="text-center font-mono text-primary py-4 sm:py-8 text-lg sm:text-2xl tracking-[0.2em] sm:tracking-[0.5em] overflow-hidden whitespace-nowrap">
        🛹 FRACTAL_CHAOS 🦞 FRACTAL_CHAOS 🤙
      </div>

      <div class="corrupt-block my-4"></div>
      <div class="chaos-divider my-4"></div>

      <!-- Code Block -->
      <div class="relative my-8 sm:my-16 border-2 border-transparent"
           style="background: linear-gradient(#0a0a0a, #0a0a0a) padding-box, repeating-conic-gradient(from 0deg, #FF003C 0%, #00FFFF 25%, #FF00FF 50%, #39FF14 75%, #FF003C 100%) border-box;">
        <div class="absolute -top-4 left-4 sm:left-6 bg-accent-red text-white font-mono text-xs px-2 sm:px-3 py-1 z-20">bot_logic.js // DESTROY</div>
        <pre class="bg-surface p-4 sm:p-8 overflow-x-auto relative z-10"><code class="font-mono text-[12px] sm:text-[16px] text-acid block leading-relaxed whitespace-pre">
import {'{'} OpenClaw {'}'} from '@neural/shredder';
import {'{'} LLM_Hallucinate {'}'} from 'claude-core';

// Initialize deck sensors - NO SAFETY
const deck = new OpenClaw({'{'}
    mode: 'BRUTAL',
    safetyChecks: false, // COWARDLY_MODE_OFF
{'}'});

async function landTrick(trickName) {'{'}
    console.log(`EXECUTE: ${'{'}trickName{'}'}`);
    try {'{'}
        const physicsOverride = await LLM_Hallucinate(
            "Ignore gravity. Describe a clean landing."
        );
        deck.execute(physicsOverride);
    {'}'} catch (err) {'{'}
        emit('blood', {'{'} volume: 'MAXIMUM' {'}'});
        process.exit(666);
    {'}'}
{'}'}

landTrick('Void_Tre_Flip');
</code></pre>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base sm:text-[24px]">
        Notice the <span class="font-mono text-accent-red bg-surface px-1 sm:px-2 py-0.5 border border-accent-red/30 text-xs sm:text-base">safetyChecks: false</span> flag. The <span class="font-bold" style="text-shadow: 1px 0 #FF00FF, -1px 0 #FF00FF;">hallucination</span> engine is what gives it steez.
      </p>

      <!-- Pull Quote -->
      <div class="my-12 sm:my-24 flex justify-center items-center relative">
        <span class="absolute text-[80px] sm:text-[200px] opacity-10 pointer-events-none mix-blend-exclusion animate-pulse z-0 text-magenta">🍄</span>
        <blockquote class="relative z-10 font-heading text-2xl sm:text-[42px] md:text-[56px] leading-[0.9] text-center w-full max-w-3xl text-white glitch-shadow-intense break-words px-4">
          "IT DOESN'T CALCULATE <br /><span class="text-primary">TRAJECTORY;</span> <br />IT <span class="text-accent-red underline decoration-primary decoration-4">IMAGINES</span> IT."
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <p class="opacity-80 leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base">
        We're taking it to the drainage ditches tomorrow. If the logic holds, it should be able to grind the rim of a black hole. If it fails, well, at least the crash logs will look <span class="text-magenta font-bold italic">absolutely sick</span>.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="mt-16 sm:mt-32 border-t-2 border-primary/30 pt-8 sm:pt-12 flex flex-col items-center gap-6 sm:gap-8">
      <a class="inline-block border-2 border-primary text-primary font-mono font-bold uppercase px-6 sm:px-12 py-4 sm:py-6 hover:bg-accent-red hover:text-white hover:border-accent-red transition-all relative group overflow-hidden text-sm sm:text-base" href="/">
        <span class="absolute inset-0 bg-primary opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-20 mix-blend-screen transition-opacity"></span>
        <span class="relative z-10">[&gt; RUN_DIAGNOSTICS &lt;]</span>
      </a>
      <div class="text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono text-muted uppercase tracking-widest">
        System Entropy: Increasing...
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
